The core language-detection engine, BuildPlan data model, Provider
interface, and the structure of the language-specific providers
(Go, Node.js, Python, static, shell) were originally developed in
Railpack and have been adapted for the Theo platform. Much of the
architecture, naming, and many implementation details preserved in
this repository originate from that work.

We are grateful to the Railway team and the Railpack community for
publishing their work under a permissive license, which made this
project possible.

Modifications made for theo-packs include (non-exhaustive):

  * Removal of the Railpack CLI and direct BuildKit/LLB integration;
    theo-packs emits a Dockerfile and delegates image construction
    to the downstream Theo build pipeline (Argo Workflow + external
    BuildKit/Kaniko).
  * Replacement of the multi-module layout (core + railpack) with a
    single Go module (github.com/usetheo/theopacks) plus a single
    CLI binary (cmd/theopacks-generate) used by the build cluster.
  * Workspace-aware Dockerfile generation for Node monorepos
    (turbo / pnpm / npm workspaces) driven by THEOPACKS_APP_NAME
    and THEOPACKS_APP_PATH.
  * Configuration namespace renamed from RAILPACK_* / railpack.json
    to THEOPACKS_* / theopacks.json.
  * Reduced dependency surface and an internal-only file system
    abstraction tailored to the Theo build environment.

All modifications are © 2025-2026 The Theo Authors and are released
under the same Apache License, Version 2.0.

