Per-provider derivations (theo-packs ↔ Railpack)

The following provider packages were added in the multi-language expansion
and incorporate detection logic, manifest parsing, and version-resolution
priorities derived from the upstream Railpack provider of the same name:

  * core/providers/rust/    — derived from railpack/core/providers/rust
  * core/providers/java/    — derived from railpack/core/providers/java
  * core/providers/dotnet/  — derived from railpack/core/providers/dotnet
  * core/providers/ruby/    — derived from railpack/core/providers/ruby
  * core/providers/php/     — derived from railpack/core/providers/php
  * core/providers/deno/    — derived from railpack/core/providers/deno

The Plan() bodies in each of those packages were rewritten from scratch
to match theo-packs' base-image-per-language strategy (rust:<v>-bookworm,
eclipse-temurin:<v>, ruby:<v>-bookworm-slim, php:<v>-cli-bookworm,
mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/{sdk,aspnet,runtime}:<v>, denoland/deno:bin-<v>)
because Railpack uses mise-driven LLB primitives whereas theo-packs emits
Dockerfiles with explicit base images. Test fixtures and example projects
that were ported retain their structure and licensing terms; new fixtures
are © 2025-2026 The Theo Authors.

The five original providers (golang, node, python, staticfile, shell) and
the test/configuration scaffolding around them are also originally derived
from Railpack as noted in the general acknowledgement above.
